metadata.name: Cathedral of Metz
metadata.description:
The cathedral of Metz located in France, is made of Jaumont stone. This natural material reacts particular to the light vibrancy. This picture makes part of my intimate landscapes series. I have always admired this monument. While taking the photo, I observe the  reflection of the radiance coming from the cathedral arches. 
It tried to capture the moment when the sunset sunlight reflected on the cathedral and how its shadows sculpted the volumes and details

Photo taken with a Nikon D810 
Lens : NIKON PC Nikkor 19 mm f/4E ED
Dimension : 7360px x 4912px
1/1 NFT
